From: Alexandru Costache <alexandru@balena.io>
Date: Wed, 22 Sep 2021 15:30:04 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] ext4: add cond_resched() to __ext4_find_entry()

To avoid soft-lockup.

Backported from http://lkml.iu.edu/hypermail/linux/kernel/2002.3/05148.html

Signed-off-by: Alexandru Costache <alexandru@balena.io>
---
 fs/ext4/namei.c | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/fs/ext4/namei.c b/fs/ext4/namei.c
index 1c6275363daa..0841644eadec 100644
--- a/fs/ext4/namei.c
+++ b/fs/ext4/namei.c
@@ -1402,6 +1402,7 @@ static struct buffer_head * ext4_find_entry (struct inode *dir,
 		/*
 		 * We deal with the read-ahead logic here.
 		 */
+		cond_resched();
 		if (ra_ptr >= ra_max) {
 			/* Refill the readahead buffer */
 			ra_ptr = 0;
